text: Muricopsis gorii is a species of small sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusks in the family Muricidae, the rock snails. This species was first described in 2012 based on specimens from the south of the island of São Tomé, São Tomé and Príncipe.Houart R. (2012) Description of Muricopsis (Muricopsis) gorii (Gastropoda: Muricidae: Muricopsinae) from southern São Tomé.
